g.text: Alternative power connectors and basic circuit protection

g.text: Use a fuse apropriate for your power supply and current consumption.

g.desc: Use a fuse apropriate for your power supply and current consumption.

g.text: Example: If you use a 5V 3A power supply, acidetaly reverse polarity and use a fuse larger than 3A

g.desc: Example: If you use a 5V 3A power supply, acidetaly reverse polarity and use a fuse larger than 3A

g.text: the zener diode might burn before the fuse breaks.

g.desc: the zener diode might burn before the fuse breaks.

g.text: This is because some power supplys will be able to clamp the current to its max rating

g.desc: This is because some power supplys will be able to clamp the current to its max rating

g.text: while dropping the voltage to in this case the forward voltage of the zener.

g.desc: while dropping the voltage to in this case the forward voltage of the zener.

g.text: Lets say a forward voltage of 1V current of 3A so 3W of power.

g.desc: Lets say a forward voltage of 1V current of 3A so 3W of power.

g.text: The total power dissipation(Tamb ≤ 25 °C) of the zener with the sandard footprint is 0.682W.

g.desc: The total power dissipation(Tamb ≤ 25 °C) of the zener with the sandard footprint is 0.682W.

g.text: The zener will let out the magic smoke and then all the other components that can not withstand reverse polarity.

g.desc: The zener will let out the magic smoke and then all the other components that can not withstand reverse polarity.

g.text: You could add a diode protect against reverse polarity but then you lose at best 0.5V over the diode.

g.desc: You could add a diode protect against reverse polarity but then you lose at best 0.5V over the diode.

g.text: The fuse and zenner also protects against reverse polarity.

g.desc: The fuse and zenner also protects against reverse polarity.

g.text: A fuse is cheap to replace so I did not add it.
